---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy | The Lawn Guide"
  description="What cookies The Lawn Guide uses (almost none), and what your retailer cookies do when you click an affiliate link."
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-20">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-terracotta-600 font-medium mb-4">Cookies</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-forest-900 leading-tight tracking-tight">
        Cookie Policy
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p class="text-xl text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-8 font-serif italic">
        This site uses no cookies of its own. Affiliate links you click set cookies belonging to the destination retailer.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies set by The Lawn Guide</h2>
      <p>
        None. The analytics service we use (Cloudflare Web Analytics) is cookie-free by design. There are no advertising cookies, no Google Analytics, no Facebook Pixel.
      </p>
      <p>
        This is why you don't see a cookie banner. UK and EU law only requires cookie consent banners when sites set non-essential cookies. This site doesn't, so there's nothing to consent to.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party cookies (affiliate links)</h2>
      <p>
        When you click an affiliate link to a retailer like Amazon, Crocus, or any of the affiliate network partners (Awin, CJ), that retailer may set cookies on your browser to attribute any subsequent purchase to this site. These cookies are owned and controlled by the retailer, not by us.
      </p>
      <p>
        Typical affiliate cookies last between 24 hours (Amazon) and 90 days (some Awin merchants), and contain only a tracking ID. They don't contain personal information.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can clear these cookies any time through your browser settings, or block third-party cookies entirely if you prefer.
      </p>

      <h2>Newsletter and email</h2>
      <p>
        The newsletter signup form does not set cookies. If you subscribe, your email is stored by our email service provider under their own privacy and cookie policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:hello@lawnguide.co.uk">hello@lawnguide.co.uk</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="text-sm text-ink-500 mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-forest-200/60">
        Last updated: May 2026
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>